  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 200°C/ 180°C (fan)/ gas 6 and boil a kettle</p><p>Pat your <strong>pork belly</strong> dry with <strong>kitchen paper</strong></p><p>Score the fatty side of the pork belly in a criss-cross pattern by drawing a sharp knife through the skin, deep enough to reach the meat below</p><p>Season with a very generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and rub it deep into the criss-cross pattern</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC2447Step-1-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC2447Step-1-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC2447Step-1-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC2447Step-1-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC2447Step-1-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) over a high heat</p><p>Once very hot, add the <strong>pork belly</strong>, fat side down and cook for 3-4 min or until coloured and crispy, then flip and cook for 2 min on the other side</p><p>Line a baking tray with <strong>tin foil</strong></p><p>Once the pork is done, transfer to the tray and put the tray in the oven for 40-45 min or until cooked through (no pink meat!)</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC2447Step-2-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC2447Step-2-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC2447Step-2-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC2447Step-2-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC2447Step-2-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Whilst the pork is cooking, peel and finely chop your <strong>shallot[s]</strong></p><p>Add a large knob of <strong>butter </strong>to a bowl with 50ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[75ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[100ml]</span> <strong>boiled water</strong></p><p>Once the butter has melted, add the <strong>chopped shallot</strong>, <strong>panko breadcrumbs</strong> and <strong>dried sage </strong>to the bowl</p><p>Season with a generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong>, give everything a good mix up and set aside to absorb – this is your <strong>stuffing mixture</strong></p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC2447Step-3-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC2447Step-3-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC2447Step-3-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC2447Step-3-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC2447Step-3-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Cut your <strong>potatoes</strong> (skins on) into thin chips</p><p>Add the <strong>chips</strong> to one side of a baking tray with a generous drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong> and give everything a good mix up</p><p>Add spoonfuls of the <strong>stuffing mixture</strong> to the other side of the tray</p><p>Put the tray in the oven for 20-25 min or until everything is golden and crisp</p><p>Tip: Cooking for 3 or more? Use 2 trays!</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC2447Step-4-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC2447Step-4-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC2447Step-4-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC2447Step-4-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC2447Step-4-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, peel, core and roughly chop your <strong>apple[s]</strong>, discarding the core[s]</p><p>Add the <strong>chopped apple </strong>to a pot with a lid with 100ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[125ml]</span><span class=\"text-danger\"> [150ml]</span> <strong>cold water </strong>and 2 tsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[3 tsp]</span><span class=\"text-danger\"> [4 tsp]<strong> </span>sugar</strong></p><p>Cook, covered, over a medium heat for 10-15 min or until the apple has softened</p><p>Once cooked, add a knob of<strong> butter</strong> and mash until smooth – this is your <strong>apple sauce</strong></p>",
